OL,3,CHundreds of BMA doctors' union staff
OL,4,Cwalk out on strike in pay dispute
OL,6,FHundreds of workers at the doctors'
OL,7,Funion have walked out on two-day
OL,8,Fstrike in a row over pay.
OL,10,FThe GMB union claims that British
OL,11,FMedical Association (BMA) staff have
OL,12,Fhad their pay eroded by almost 17%
OL,13,Fsince 2012.
OL,15,FIt comes after the BMA announced that
OL,16,Fresident doctors in England will walk
OL,17,Fout for six days from 7am on April 7
OL,18,Funtil April 13 in a dispute over jobs
OL,19,Fand wages.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/7
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,314,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F313A1774627872
OL,3,CHundreds of BMA doctors' union staff
OL,4,Cwalk out on strike in pay dispute
OL,6,FThe GMB said 96% of BMA staff voted in
OL,7,Ffavour of industrial action, on a
OL,8,Fturnout of 80%.
OL,10,FThe union's senior organiser, Gavin
OL,11,FDavies, said: "Staff are angry and
OL,12,Fdisappointed that the pay deal offered
OL,13,Fdoesn't match inflation and doesn't
OL,14,Fbegin to address the real terms pay
OL,15,Fcut they've experienced."
OL,17,FHe added: "BMA staff have tirelessly
OL,18,Fsupported resident doctors in their
OL,19,Ffight for improved pay. Now it's their
OL,20,Fturn to demand a fair pay deal."
OL,26,@sD@OOUwD@YO]yD@KOU|D@`O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/7
